reviewText:
Hard to say if i recommend it or not..

Good sides;
Chill music, Mysterious/fantasy back/foregrounds. Cute & well-invented companion, Main character is so sad,depressing & everything around him is hopeless in his eyes (Which i find funny/entertaining as thats exactly how you feel for most maincharacters in puzzle games, Great story & nice cutscenes, Lots of humor. pile of achivements & you get 4 tradeing cards (not worth much but hey!).

Bad sides;
It took me almost 17 hours of nonstop playing to beat haveing to look at a walkthrough constantly as 70-80% of the puzzles made no sense what so ever (Example combineing a frog to a stick) Finding myself stuck all the time. (I play alot of puzzle games but this ranks up with some of the most frustrateing ones). I also ran into a bug and had to load a save that was 2 hours away before the thing i did mess up (altho i did it right acording to the walkthru). So i'd recommend to save often and always have that 1 far-back, Backup save incase something stops working. Yes sometimes in the beginning of the game there is some cut-off sound/text when someones talking. But didin't notice anything for the rest of the game, Theres also a minor spelling issue (sometimes the character might say (in sound) I can't reach it!"
